"author_information": "Miguel de Cervantes Saavedra (1547-1616) was a Spanish novelist, poet, and playwright. His masterpiece, \"Don Quixote,\" is considered one of the most influential works of literature and a founding work of modern Western literature.",
"interesting_fact": "The First Part of *Don Quixote* was published in 1605 and gained immediate success, but Cervantes did not publish the Second Part until 1615, partly in response to a spurious sequel published by an anonymous author under the pseudonym Alonso Fernández de Avellaneda. This act of literary rivalry spurred Cervantes to complete his own vision, solidifying the novel's place in literary history."
